<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="236" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,460,701]" pageId="7" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,460,485]" pageId="7" pageNumber="236">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ngoc-Ho" box="[273,459,460,485]" pageId="7" pageNumber="236" refString="Ngoc-Ho, N. (2005) Thalassinidea (Crustacea, Decapoda) from French Polynesia. Zoosystema, 27, 47 - 83." type="journal article" year="2005">
Ngoc-Ho (
<number box="[392,451,460,485]" pageId="7" pageNumber="236" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
included provisionally among the material examined for her description of 
<taxonomicName box="[1305,1417,460,485]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianideidae" genus="Heardaxius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salvati">
<emphasis box="[1305,1417,460,485]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="236">M. salvati</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a male and female of two small incomplete specimens from 
<taxonomicName box="[838,928,496,519]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianideidae" genus="Thomassinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moorea">Moorea</taxonomicName>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[942,1140,495,520]" name="French Polynesia" pageId="7" pageNumber="236">French Polynesia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" box="[1157,1244,496,520]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="7" pageNumber="236">MNHN</collectionCode>
Th 
<number box="[1289,1347,495,520]" pageId="7" pageNumber="236" value="1302.0">1302</number>
). These were described as ‘cf. 
<taxonomicName box="[408,519,533,556]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianideidae" genus="Mictaxius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[408,519,533,556]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="236">Mictaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. 
<number box="[568,584,532,556]" pageId="7" pageNumber="236" value="1.0">1</number>
’ by 
<bibRefCitation author="Poore" box="[636,1042,532,557]" pageId="7" pageNumber="236" refString="Poore, G. C. B. (1997) A review of the thalassinidean families Callianideidae Kossmann, Micheleidae Sakai, and Thomassiniidae de Saint Laurent (Crustacea: Decapoda) with descriptions of fifteen new species. Zoosystema, 19, 345 - 420." type="journal article" year="1997">
Poore (
<number box="[719,780,532,556]" pageId="7" pageNumber="236" value="1997.0">1997</number>
: 
<number box="[792,893,532,556]" pageId="7" pageNumber="236" value="409.0" valueMax="410.0" valueMin="408.0">408–410</number>
, figs 
<number box="[956,984,532,556]" pageId="7" pageNumber="236" value="33.0">33</number>
H–J)
</bibRefCitation>
. The same individuals and species name were listed as ‘ 
<taxonomicName box="[392,535,567,592]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianideidae" genus="Thomassinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[392,535,567,592]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="236">Thomassinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. 
<number box="[584,598,568,592]" pageId="7" pageNumber="236" value="1.0">1</number>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Poore" box="[614,757,568,592]" pageId="7" pageNumber="236" refString="Poore, G. C. B. (1997) A review of the thalassinidean families Callianideidae Kossmann, Micheleidae Sakai, and Thomassiniidae de Saint Laurent (Crustacea: Decapoda) with descriptions of fifteen new species. Zoosystema, 19, 345 - 420." type="journal article" year="1997">
Poore, 
<number box="[696,757,568,592]" pageId="7" pageNumber="236" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)’ by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai" box="[815,1017,567,592]" pageId="7" pageNumber="236" refString="Sakai, K. (2011) Axioidea of the world and a reconsideration of the Callianassoidea (Decapoda, Thalassinidea, Callianassida). Crustaceana Monographs, 13, 1 - 616." type="journal article" year="2011">
Sakai (
<number box="[894,954,568,592]" pageId="7" pageNumber="236" value="2011.0">2011</number>
: 
<number box="[966,1010,567,592]" pageId="7" pageNumber="236" value="537.0">537</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
on the basis of the linea thalassinica being incomplete. Besides being gonochoristic (a male and female were reported), the incomplete linea thalassinica, eyestalk, uropodal exopod and telson differ from the 
<typeStatus box="[889,937,640,664]" pageId="7" pageNumber="236">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[974,1083,639,664]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianideidae" genus="Heardaxius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salvati">
<emphasis box="[974,1083,639,664]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="236">H. salvati</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The uropod certainly excludes them from 
<taxonomicName box="[275,418,676,701]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianideidae" genus="Thomassinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[275,418,676,701]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="236">Thomassinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
